WEBVTT

00:05.533 --> 00:07.401
Awkward silence.

00:07.403 --> 00:08.685
Sheldon on his phone.

00:08.687 --> 00:09.720
No touching.

00:09.722 --> 00:13.123
Somebody's having date night.

00:13.125 --> 00:15.209
It's actually steamier
than it looks.

00:15.211 --> 00:18.078
Sheldon's looking up the phallic
symbolism of root vegetables

00:18.080 --> 00:19.797
in Renaissance paintings.

00:19.799 --> 00:21.448
Oh, no, I got bored
with that.

00:21.450 --> 00:25.419
I'm just browsing
cuticle scissors on Amazon.

00:26.371 --> 00:28.005
How do you
not tear off his clothes

00:28.007 --> 00:30.557
and take him right here
on this table?

00:30.559 --> 00:33.260
If you do that, I'll scream.

00:36.431 --> 00:38.632
Sheldon, I have some
exciting news to tell you.

00:38.634 --> 00:39.783
That makes two of us.

00:39.785 --> 00:41.268
My new cuticle scissors
will be here

00:41.270 --> 00:43.153
in one to two business days.

00:43.155 --> 00:45.722
Come on, one.

00:45.724 --> 00:47.825
I've been invited to
consult on an experiment

00:47.827 --> 00:50.194
at your university
for a few months.

00:50.196 --> 00:51.328
Isn't that great?

00:51.330 --> 00:52.913
We could have lunch together.

00:52.915 --> 00:54.315
We could carpool.

00:54.317 --> 00:56.467
You know, riding with Leonard

00:56.469 --> 00:58.736
has gotten
a little tedious lately.

00:58.738 --> 01:02.206
Th-The only car game he ever
wants to play is the Quiet Game.

01:02.208 --> 01:03.307
And he's terrible at it.

01:03.309 --> 01:05.459
I always win.

01:06.845 --> 01:08.729
So, you're okay with this?

01:08.731 --> 01:10.397
Well, why wouldn't I be?

01:10.399 --> 01:12.433
Well, this project
would have us working

01:12.435 --> 01:14.468
in close proximity
to one another.

01:14.470 --> 01:15.969
And there's the vulgar adage

01:15.971 --> 01:19.640
that one should not
defecate where one eats.

01:19.642 --> 01:21.975
My father used to say
that all the time.

01:21.977 --> 01:25.162
That and, um, "Who does one
have to orally gratify

01:25.164 --> 01:27.881
to get a drink around here?"

01:29.234 --> 01:31.719
But what does that have to do

01:31.721 --> 01:33.637
with you working
at the university?

01:33.639 --> 01:36.240
Sheldon, "Don't defecate
where you eat,"

01:36.242 --> 01:38.275
means don't have a
romantic relationship

01:38.277 --> 01:39.877
in the workplace.

01:41.079 --> 01:43.063
Really?

01:45.767 --> 01:47.384
Yes.

01:47.386 --> 01:48.469
Huh.

01:48.471 --> 01:50.788
Yeah, I always
took it literally.

01:50.790 --> 01:53.623
That's why I have never
once moved my bowels

01:53.625 --> 01:55.993
in this or any restaurant.

01:55.995 --> 01:57.945
Hmm.

01:57.947 --> 01:59.980
I'm relieved that you
don't have a problem

01:59.982 --> 02:01.265
with us working together.

02:01.267 --> 02:03.517
Not as relieved
as I'm about to be.

02:04.519 --> 02:06.754
It's a brave new world,
little lady.

02:09.190 --> 02:12.826
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

02:12.828 --> 02:16.163
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

02:16.165 --> 02:17.814
♪ The Earth began to cool

02:17.816 --> 02:20.334
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

02:20.336 --> 02:23.003
♪ We built the Wall
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

02:23.005 --> 02:25.689
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

02:25.691 --> 02:27.574
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

02:27.576 --> 02:28.342
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

02:28.343 --> 02:32.343
<font color=#00FF00>♪ The Big Bang Theory 7x05 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>The Workplace Proximity</font>
