02:32.368 --> 02:37.368
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

02:37.819 --> 02:39.386
Are you crazy?

02:39.388 --> 02:40.437
You don't want

02:40.439 --> 02:42.306
your girlfriend
at work with you.

02:42.308 --> 02:45.008
Hell Clam.

02:45.010 --> 02:46.527
Why not?

02:46.529 --> 02:49.113
Hairy Fairy.

02:49.115 --> 02:50.681
I think it could be romantic.

02:50.683 --> 02:52.650
You know, my parents met
at his place of work.

02:52.652 --> 02:55.686
Your father's a gynecologist.

02:55.688 --> 02:56.870
I know.

02:56.872 --> 02:59.823
What started as a pap smear
turned into a date.

03:01.293 --> 03:02.676
Which turned
into her working there,

03:02.678 --> 03:04.645
which turned into marriage,
which then turned into hatred,

03:04.647 --> 03:07.197
which continues to this day.

03:07.299 --> 03:10.067
Two-Eyed Cyclops.

03:10.069 --> 03:12.903
Would you please tell him
this isn't a good idea?

03:12.905 --> 03:14.271
No, no, I think it'll be great.

03:14.273 --> 03:15.889
Maybe next time he gets
conjunctivitis at work,

03:15.891 --> 03:19.943
she can hold his head and try
to put the drops in his eyes.

03:19.945 --> 03:22.429
Giant baby.

03:22.431 --> 03:24.281
That's a Raging Ogre.

03:24.283 --> 03:26.517
Yeah, I know.

03:28.520 --> 03:30.687
I'm just saying, I'd never want
to work with Bernadette.

03:30.689 --> 03:32.656
Can you imagine seeing
someone all day long

03:32.658 --> 03:34.124
and then you're
supposed to hang out

03:34.126 --> 03:35.826
with them after work, too?

03:35.828 --> 03:37.494
Hold on. We do
that all the time.

03:37.496 --> 03:39.229
You and I work together
and play together.

03:39.231 --> 03:42.883
Yeah, I know, and it drove me
into the arms of another woman.

03:44.702 --> 03:46.720
Bipolar Bear.

03:46.722 --> 03:49.606
Well, I appreciate your concern,

03:49.608 --> 03:52.810
but I won't be seeing any more
of Amy than I already do.

03:52.812 --> 03:55.095
I assume we'll deduct
any extra time we spend together

03:55.097 --> 03:57.965
at work from our weekly quota.

03:59.884 --> 04:02.553
Please let me be there
when you tell her that.

04:03.521 --> 04:05.689
Why? So you can see the
look on Amy's face

04:05.691 --> 04:07.991
when she hears
my top-notch idea?

04:07.993 --> 04:10.577
Please, oh, please,
just let me be there.

04:12.547 --> 04:15.682
So, Amy, what are you gonna
be working on at Caltech?

04:15.684 --> 04:17.468
I'm leading a study to see

04:17.470 --> 04:19.369
if deficiency of the
monoamine oxidase enzyme

04:19.370 --> 04:21.445
leads to paralyzing
fear in monkeys.

04:21.470 --> 04:22.340
Oh.

04:22.341 --> 04:25.159
If they're anything like humans,
the answer's yes.

04:25.161 --> 04:27.578
Wait, you've-you've done
this experiment on humans?

04:27.580 --> 04:30.264
You mean like death row inmates
with nothing to lose?

04:30.366 --> 04:33.083
No, that would be unethical.

04:34.619 --> 04:36.587
You know,
not a lot of people know this,

04:36.589 --> 04:37.838
but the monoamine oxidase enzyme

04:37.840 --> 04:39.790
was discovered by a woman,
Mary Bernheim.

04:42.277 --> 04:43.543
That's right.

04:43.545 --> 04:46.546
My phone is just
as smart as you guys.

04:48.317 --> 04:49.449
Amy, Bernadette, Penny.

04:49.451 --> 04:51.151
Amy, Bernadette,
Penny.

04:51.153 --> 04:53.537
Amy, Bernadette, Penny.

04:53.539 --> 04:56.306
He's never gonna
stop doing that, is he?

04:56.308 --> 04:57.441
I don't mind.

04:57.443 --> 04:59.109
I'm hoping to put
his love of repetition

04:59.111 --> 05:00.861
to good use someday.

05:03.247 --> 05:05.232
Hi. Um...

05:05.234 --> 05:06.400
I've reconsidered.

05:06.402 --> 05:07.901
Uh, you can't work
where I work.

05:07.903 --> 05:09.269
Enjoy the rest
of your evening.

05:09.271 --> 05:10.904
Sheldon.

05:10.906 --> 05:13.123
I-I already signed
the contract.

05:13.125 --> 05:14.524
I cashed a check.

05:14.526 --> 05:16.576
Mmm... you are not going

05:16.578 --> 05:18.428
to come out of
this looking good.

05:18.430 --> 05:19.663
Sheldon,
I don't understand.

05:19.665 --> 05:21.581
I thought you said
you were fine with it.

05:21.583 --> 05:22.699
Well, I was.

05:22.701 --> 05:24.334
But that was before
Howard explained to me

05:24.336 --> 05:26.470
how awful it would be
if he had to work

05:26.472 --> 05:28.138
with his significant other.

05:28.140 --> 05:30.724
He said what?

05:30.726 --> 05:32.676
Now, don't be insulted.

05:32.678 --> 05:36.897
He just thinks too much of you
would be mind-numbingly tedious.

05:36.899 --> 05:40.067
Excuse me, I need to have
a chat with my husband.

05:40.069 --> 05:41.902
Yeah, well, now,
well... keep it short.

05:41.904 --> 05:45.439
Fr-From what I gather,
brevity is your friend.

05:46.574 --> 05:48.742
So, are we good here?

05:48.744 --> 05:50.327
No, we're not good here.

05:50.329 --> 05:51.828
I am working on this project.

05:51.830 --> 05:54.081
Yeah, and you can't tell her
what she can and cannot do.

05:54.083 --> 05:56.099
Last week, you told Leonard
he couldn't wear

05:56.101 --> 05:58.301
his Wookiee jacket
out in public.

05:58.303 --> 05:59.519
That's different.

05:59.521 --> 06:01.455
I'm not going to the mall
with someone dressed

06:01.457 --> 06:03.540
dumb space bear.

06:05.576 --> 06:07.627
Sheldon, you don't have to worry
about me bothering you.

06:07.629 --> 06:08.879
I'll be in a different building.

06:08.881 --> 06:10.747
And we don't even have
to have lunch together.

06:10.749 --> 06:11.865
Really?

06:11.867 --> 06:14.518
Yes. Before all things,
I'm a scientist.

06:14.520 --> 06:16.970
I'm just there to do my work
and, with a little luck,

06:16.972 --> 06:19.606
scare the living crap
out of some monkeys.

06:19.608 --> 06:23.143
Hmm.

06:23.145 --> 06:25.812
You sure your mothlike
personality won't be drawn

06:25.814 --> 06:28.565
to this blazing fire
that is myself?

06:31.536 --> 06:33.787
More and more sure.

06:33.789 --> 06:36.873
Well, then, you
have my permission.

06:36.875 --> 06:37.958
I didn't ask
for your permission.

06:37.960 --> 06:39.159
Too late. No backsies.

06:41.612 --> 06:44.414
No, no, listen to me.
Sheldon misunderstood.

06:44.416 --> 06:45.382
What I meant was,

06:45.384 --> 06:46.449
if we worked together,

06:46.451 --> 06:48.118
there'd be too much
of me for you,

06:48.120 --> 06:50.253
not the other way around.

06:50.255 --> 06:52.723
Howard, if you're going
to lie to your wife,

06:52.725 --> 06:55.325
don't start the sentence
with "Sheldon misunderstood."

06:56.878 --> 06:58.011
That's a dead giveaway.

06:58.013 --> 06:59.930
Well?

06:59.932 --> 07:01.131
Okay, fine.

07:01.133 --> 07:02.899
I did say that,
and I think it's true.

07:02.901 --> 07:05.018
I think if we worked together
and lived together,

07:05.020 --> 07:06.520
we'd get sick of each other.

07:06.522 --> 07:08.105
Yeah, but to be fair,
he only said the part

07:08.107 --> 07:09.189
about him
getting sick of you.

07:09.191 --> 07:11.024
For the love of God, why?!

07:15.213 --> 07:17.864
What exactly do you
think you'd get sick of?

07:17.866 --> 07:20.016
His only options here
are to fake a heart attack

07:20.018 --> 07:22.385
or have a real one.

07:22.387 --> 07:25.655
It-it's nothing
in particular. I...

07:25.657 --> 07:27.824
Is it my voice?
Am I too bossy?

07:27.826 --> 07:28.959
What...?

07:28.961 --> 07:31.878
My arm is feeling numb.

07:32.797 --> 07:35.782
Nailed it.

07:35.784 --> 07:39.386
That's the wrong arm for
a heart attack, doofus.

07:41.222 --> 07:44.357
My point is, I'm sure
there are things about me

07:44.359 --> 07:46.643
that would drive you crazy
if you had to deal

07:46.645 --> 07:48.395
with them all day long.

07:48.397 --> 07:50.597
Like looking me in the
eye and lying to me?

07:50.599 --> 07:52.149
Oh, well, come on, I just...

07:52.151 --> 07:55.402
Where am I supposed to
look when I lie to you?

07:55.404 --> 07:57.754
Find somewhere else
to sleep tonight.

07:57.756 --> 07:59.906
Oh, Bernie...

08:06.864 --> 08:10.467
If it makes you feel any better,
Amy and I are fine.

08:13.070 --> 08:15.238
I mean, really good.

08:17.475 --> 08:19.843
So, boys, how was
the pajama party?

08:19.845 --> 08:23.730
You guys jump on the bed
and sing into hair brushes?

08:23.732 --> 08:25.932
It wasn't a pajama party.

08:25.934 --> 08:28.435
It was just a couple of bros
hanging out, giggling,

08:28.437 --> 08:31.521
eating cookie dough
and watching <i>Princess Bride.</i>

08:33.073 --> 08:34.607
Please, stop talking.

08:36.244 --> 08:38.861
As you wish.

08:42.667 --> 08:44.734
I mean, you know, Sheldon,
none of this would've happened

08:44.736 --> 08:46.203
if I hadn't tried
to help you.

08:46.205 --> 08:48.788
Uh, it also wouldn't
have happened

08:48.790 --> 08:50.290
if, in the early universe,

08:50.292 --> 08:53.793
hydrogen was a little more
common or a little less common.

08:53.795 --> 08:56.279
This is fun. Your turn.

08:57.265 --> 08:58.598
Gentlemen.
Hey, Amy.

08:58.600 --> 09:00.283
Hello.

09:00.285 --> 09:01.685
That was kind of icy.

09:01.687 --> 09:03.336
You two okay?

09:03.338 --> 09:04.354
Oh, we're fine.

09:04.356 --> 09:05.772
As Howard advised,

09:05.774 --> 09:07.974
she's merely respecting our
professional boundaries.

09:07.976 --> 09:08.942
Smart.

09:08.944 --> 09:10.544
Take relationship advice
from a man

09:10.546 --> 09:12.963
who spent last night
braiding Raj's hair.

09:15.432 --> 09:18.451
Yeah, you make
a good point.

09:18.453 --> 09:20.654
It would appear
I was worried for nothing.

09:20.656 --> 09:22.205
Look at her, desperately wishing

09:22.207 --> 09:24.157
she was over here
at the cool table.

09:26.577 --> 09:28.328
Don't worry, little moth.

09:28.330 --> 09:30.630
The flame will come to you.

09:32.833 --> 09:34.568
Oh, uh...

09:34.570 --> 09:36.386
on the off chance that
Bernadette doesn't call back

09:36.388 --> 09:37.771
and apologize,
how do you feel

09:37.773 --> 09:39.673
about Mexican food
for dinner tonight?

09:39.675 --> 09:41.841
I-I don't know.
Sounds kind of heavy.

09:41.843 --> 09:44.811
That's 'cause you always
fill up on chips.

09:44.813 --> 09:47.480
And this is Dr. Gunderson
from Stockholm.

09:47.482 --> 09:49.032
Ah, Sweden.

09:49.034 --> 09:50.734
Yeah, home of my favorite Muppet

09:50.736 --> 09:53.720
and, uh,
second favorite meatball.

09:57.141 --> 10:01.344
Okay, the Nordic reputation for
lack of humor is well-founded.

10:02.813 --> 10:05.582
Boy, is his name Gunderson
or No-Funderson?

10:06.834 --> 10:09.069
Where are we going
with this, Dr. Cooper?

10:09.071 --> 10:11.104
Oh, please, I'm your boyfriend.

10:11.106 --> 10:13.556
You call me Sheldon.

10:13.558 --> 10:16.159
That's right,
I am in a boy-girl relationship

10:16.161 --> 10:18.929
with this cute little
lump of wool.

10:18.931 --> 10:20.046
Sheldon...

10:20.048 --> 10:21.765
It's a physical
relationship, too.

10:21.767 --> 10:25.518
Hand-holding, hugging...
even on hot days.

10:25.520 --> 10:27.387
Ow.

10:28.172 --> 10:29.539
Okay, here's a new one.

10:29.541 --> 10:31.141
Apparently now
we kick each other

10:31.143 --> 10:32.776
in the shin under the table.

10:34.478 --> 10:37.013
How do you like it
when I do it to you?

10:38.399 --> 10:41.067
Not so much, huh?

