10:53.499 --> 10:55.884
Test subject D7,

10:55.886 --> 10:58.536
aka Betsy, fear response study.

10:58.538 --> 11:02.390
Image number one: Frenchman
on bicycle carrying baguettes.

11:05.394 --> 11:08.396
No visible reaction.

11:08.398 --> 11:10.765
Image number two: sousaphone.

11:13.235 --> 11:14.736
Still no reaction.

11:14.738 --> 11:15.737
Okay.

11:15.739 --> 11:17.372
Let's kick things up a notch.

11:17.374 --> 11:20.091
Image number three: crocodile
with a mouthful of monkeys.

11:24.079 --> 11:27.132
Okay, now we're talking.

11:27.134 --> 11:29.067
Dr. Fowler?

11:29.069 --> 11:31.136
What do you want, Sheldon?

11:31.138 --> 11:33.221
Well, I'm done
with work, so...

11:34.424 --> 11:36.358
Oh, sorry, sorry, sorry.

11:36.360 --> 11:39.093
Sorry. Uh...

11:39.095 --> 11:40.528
Better?

11:40.530 --> 11:41.696
Oh, baguettes.

11:41.698 --> 11:43.898
Yes, I like baguettes.

11:43.900 --> 11:46.100
What exactly
are you doing?

11:46.102 --> 11:48.536
Determining baseline fear levels
in capuchin monkeys

11:48.538 --> 11:50.872
by measuring their response
to visual stimuli.

11:50.874 --> 11:52.340
So, goofing off.

11:54.910 --> 11:57.579
As I was saying, I'm done
with work and Leonard's not.

11:57.581 --> 12:00.215
So good news,
you get to take me home.

12:00.217 --> 12:01.249
Play your cards right,

12:01.251 --> 12:02.751
I'll let you drive me

12:02.753 --> 12:05.837
past the lot
where the buses park at night.

12:05.839 --> 12:07.639
I can't leave now, Sheldon.

12:07.641 --> 12:08.757
I'm very busy.

12:08.759 --> 12:10.558
Besides, why would I want
to do you a favor

12:10.560 --> 12:12.577
after the way you treated
me in the cafeteria?

12:12.579 --> 12:15.129
Image number four:
boa constrictor.

12:18.968 --> 12:21.936
What on earth
are you talking about?

12:21.938 --> 12:23.488
My behavior
in the cafeteria

12:23.490 --> 12:25.306
was delightful.

12:25.308 --> 12:27.492
Maybe your friend
Gunderson needs

12:27.494 --> 12:29.444
to head over
to IKEA and assemble

12:29.446 --> 12:32.380
a sense of humor.

12:32.382 --> 12:34.365
You embarrassed me
in front of my colleagues

12:34.367 --> 12:35.983
on my first day here.

12:36.685 --> 12:37.786
Image number five:

12:37.788 --> 12:39.187
kitten in a teacup.

12:39.189 --> 12:41.389
Oh.

12:44.960 --> 12:47.529
Oh... embarrassed you?
You know what?

12:47.531 --> 12:50.432
I don't have time for this.
Find another way home.

12:50.434 --> 12:53.451
I'm starting to get the sense
that you're angry with me.

12:53.453 --> 12:55.002
Really?
What tipped you off?

12:55.004 --> 12:56.054
Couple things, actually.

12:56.056 --> 12:57.171
Your tone of voice,
your body language...

12:57.173 --> 12:58.807
Get out.
Well, now, that.

13:00.676 --> 13:03.311
Image number six:
woman giving birth.

13:12.571 --> 13:14.188
It's 9:00.
Where you been?

13:14.190 --> 13:17.308
Oh, I had to take
the bus home.

13:17.310 --> 13:20.845
Fell asleep and missed my stop.

13:20.847 --> 13:22.647
Oh, no.

13:22.649 --> 13:26.634
Did you know that Los Angeles
has a Little Sri Lanka?

13:26.636 --> 13:28.987
I did not.

13:28.989 --> 13:31.005
Well, I do... now.

13:31.007 --> 13:33.708
They're a lovely people.

13:33.710 --> 13:37.378
Although terrifying when you
wake up face-to-face with them.

13:38.380 --> 13:39.647
If you're hungry, I brought home

13:39.649 --> 13:41.633
some mutton and coconut milk.

13:41.635 --> 13:43.618
Why'd you get that?
You hate lamb.

13:43.620 --> 13:45.687
I was asking for directions.

13:45.689 --> 13:49.207
Apparently, there was
a communication problem.

13:49.209 --> 13:52.327
I thought Amy was gonna
drive you home.

13:52.329 --> 13:53.611
Yeah, I thought so, too,

13:53.613 --> 13:55.780
but she's acting very strangely.

13:55.782 --> 13:58.783
I was discussing it with
a Sri Lankan fellow on the bus,

13:58.785 --> 14:01.870
and he hypothesized
that a tiger may have

14:01.872 --> 14:04.055
recently run across her shadow.

14:05.908 --> 14:08.343
Although he may have just been
trying to drum up business

14:08.345 --> 14:11.346
for his brother-in-law's
witch doctor practice.

14:14.266 --> 14:16.835
Okay, Sheldon, what happened
between you and Amy?

14:16.837 --> 14:20.572
Well, can you believe
she said I embarrassed her?

14:20.574 --> 14:22.657
Yeah.

14:22.659 --> 14:25.443
But you didn't
even hear the details.

14:25.445 --> 14:27.478
Sheldon...

14:29.248 --> 14:31.866
I've known you
a long time,

14:31.868 --> 14:33.284
and I'm going
to tell you this

14:33.286 --> 14:37.155
with all the love
I can possibly muster.

14:37.157 --> 14:38.156
Amy's right.

14:38.158 --> 14:39.607
You're wrong.

14:40.459 --> 14:41.659
But you don't even know...

14:41.661 --> 14:43.077
Doesn't matter.

14:43.079 --> 14:45.697
But, now, but in my defense...
Doesn't matter.

14:45.699 --> 14:47.932
You're not listening
to my side of it.

14:47.934 --> 14:50.268
Okay, fine, Sheldon.
What is your side?

14:50.270 --> 14:52.286
Well...

14:52.288 --> 14:54.789
Nope, got to go with
Amy on this one.

15:00.630 --> 15:01.679
Shrimp was spicy.

15:01.681 --> 15:03.114
You want a TUMS?

15:03.116 --> 15:04.432
You got
the tropical fruit kind?

15:04.434 --> 15:06.951
No, if I buy those, I just
go through them like candy.

15:06.953 --> 15:08.386
Tell me about it.

15:08.388 --> 15:11.105
One time, I swear
I pooped out a stick of chalk.

15:13.142 --> 15:15.360
I'll get it.
Thanks.

15:17.279 --> 15:18.363
Hi.

15:18.365 --> 15:19.530
Oh, hi.

15:19.532 --> 15:21.699
I may have overreacted.

15:21.701 --> 15:25.620
Yeah, well, I didn't
handle it so great, either.

15:25.622 --> 15:28.039
It's just sometimes I feel
like you enjoy spending time

15:28.041 --> 15:30.091
with your friends
more than with me.

15:30.093 --> 15:31.910
That's not true.
It's not?

15:31.912 --> 15:33.595
You spend all day
together at work,

15:33.597 --> 15:35.713
and then you all hang out
at night playing games,

15:35.715 --> 15:37.231
going to the comic book store.

15:37.233 --> 15:39.851
Last week, you two got
a couples massage.

15:42.488 --> 15:45.056
So, when you said you wouldn't
want to spend that much time

15:45.058 --> 15:48.026
with me, it really
hurt my feelings.

15:48.028 --> 15:49.644
Oh, wow.

15:49.646 --> 15:50.979
Yeah, no, I get that.

15:50.981 --> 15:52.113
I'm so sorry.

15:52.115 --> 15:54.866
Starting tomorrow, I am
turning over a new leaf.

15:54.868 --> 15:57.986
Time with you is my
number one priority.

15:59.990 --> 16:01.689
Why tomorrow?

16:03.191 --> 16:05.510
Well, we're real close
to finishing off

16:05.512 --> 16:07.378
the new Batman game.

16:08.514 --> 16:11.666
It is awesome.

16:13.969 --> 16:16.004
Uh, you should probably
go after her.

16:16.006 --> 16:17.755
Should I go after you?

16:17.757 --> 16:19.924
No!

16:21.593 --> 16:24.095
Thanks for getting me
in trouble.

16:26.899 --> 16:28.266
Amy.

16:29.068 --> 16:30.284
Amy.

16:31.070 --> 16:33.104
Amy.

16:34.723 --> 16:37.325
Sheldon, what are you
doing here so late?

16:37.327 --> 16:39.193
I couldn't sleep
because I kept thinking

16:39.195 --> 16:41.446
about what happened
earlier between us.

16:42.247 --> 16:45.616
Also, I had one heck
of a bus nap.

16:46.752 --> 16:47.902
Oh, speaking of which,

16:47.904 --> 16:50.788
do you want some mutton
and coconut milk?

16:50.790 --> 16:51.856
No.

16:51.858 --> 16:54.625
Well, I cannot give
this stuff away.

16:54.627 --> 16:57.078
What do you want?

16:57.080 --> 17:00.648
Amy, this isn't easy to say.

17:01.767 --> 17:04.752
All relationships are difficult,

17:04.753 --> 17:07.689
but even more so
when you're in one

17:07.691 --> 17:09.523
with a person who struggles

17:09.526 --> 17:11.858
with everyday
social interactions.

17:11.861 --> 17:13.528
And frankly...

17:13.530 --> 17:15.146
who can strike some people

17:15.147 --> 17:17.665
as being kind of a weirdo.

17:17.666 --> 17:19.650
Sheldon...

17:19.652 --> 17:21.652
you're not a weirdo.

17:21.654 --> 17:24.271
I wasn't speaking about me.

17:26.308 --> 17:28.442
I mean, honestly,
there's no telling

17:28.444 --> 17:30.078
what will set you off.

17:30.080 --> 17:32.296
You know, introducing
myself as your boyfriend.

17:32.298 --> 17:35.550
Giving you the opportunity
to drive me home.

17:35.552 --> 17:37.618
Breaking the ice
with your colleagues

17:37.620 --> 17:40.788
using ethnic humor,
the funniest kind of humor.

17:42.558 --> 17:44.225
What's your point?

17:44.227 --> 17:46.627
My point is, we're a couple.

17:46.629 --> 17:48.362
And...

17:48.364 --> 17:50.481
I like you for who you are.

17:50.483 --> 17:52.366
Quirks and all.

17:54.103 --> 17:55.653
I like you, too.

17:55.655 --> 17:58.189
Well, I should hope so.

17:58.191 --> 18:00.324
I don't see anyone else
banging on this door

18:00.326 --> 18:02.827
to put up with your nonsense.

18:06.982 --> 18:09.584
Not even a good-bye?

18:09.586 --> 18:11.085
You see,
that's the kind of thing

18:11.087 --> 18:13.621
that makes people
think you're weird.

18:13.623 --> 18:15.423
Poor kid.

18:15.425 --> 18:17.508
She just doesn't see it.

18:27.609 --> 18:28.692
I'm not apologizing
to Howard.

18:28.694 --> 18:30.343
He can come beg me
on his knees.

18:30.345 --> 18:31.695
Sheldon, too.

18:31.697 --> 18:34.197
If I see him at work,
I'm just going to ignore him.

18:34.199 --> 18:36.033
All right, don't worry.
I talked to Leonard.

18:36.035 --> 18:38.802
He is gonna sit the guys down
and set them straight.

18:38.804 --> 18:40.821
Laser's warmed up.

18:40.897 --> 18:41.929
Pull!

